    "The selection of Gen AI input, along this continuum from general to custom inputs, represents the first major decision for firms seeking to implement Gen AI solutions.",
    "1 Second, it is also important to consider how much human (or programmed) augmentation is necessary before deploying Gen AI output.",
    "For example, some firms might deploy Chat-GPT 4.0 for communications with their employees and affiliates and provide the resulting responses with little or no human augmentation.",
    "Other firms instead might prefer Grammarly, a Gen AI-based writing assistant, for such purposes.",
    "Unlike ChatGPT, Grammarly offers some automated restrictions, such as intervening to suppress responses to offensive prompts."
  ],
